Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Peel and slice @carrots{1}(sliced into thin coins on a diagonal).

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast until lightly browned, about ~{20%minutes}. Toss halfway through.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%oz} into 1-inch cubes. Place in a medium #pot{} with enough water to cover by 1 inch and a large pinch of @salt{large pinch}. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced with a knife, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%oz}. Strip leaves off @thyme{1/4%oz} and discard stems. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large ovenproof pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook until golden brown, about ~{6%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. In same pan, heat another drizzle of olive oil over medium heat. Add onions and season with salt and pepper. Cook until softened, about ~{6%minutes}.

Add 1/4 cup water, garlic, @peas{4%oz}, and thyme to pan. Cook until very soft, about another ~{3%minutes}. Sprinkle 1/2 tbsp @flour{1%tbsp} (we sent more) onto onion mixture and stir ~{1%minute}. Add 1/2 cup water and @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Stir until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add mushrooms and stir to combine.

> If your pan is not ovenproof, transfer mixture to a baking dish.

With a #fork{} or #potato masher{}, mash potatoes with 1/4 cup @milk{1%box} (we sent more) and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread potatoes over mushroom mixture and sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}.

Bake until cheese has melted and pie is bubbly, about ~{5%minutes}. Serve with roasted carrots.